    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "For networks that have already passed the Merge, it's best to drive Erigon by CL from the start. The alternative that you're describing, namely to first sync all pre-Merge blocks, relies on block gossip (at least when Erigon block snapshots end before the Merge). EIP-3675 [prohibits](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3675#network) block gossip after the Merge, rendering this strategy brittle and depending on a small fraction of peers who are left not updated with Ropsten Terminal Total Difficulty and still gossiping. Moreover, with PR #5172 such sync without a CL node will be disabled.\r\n\r\nTL;DR: Connect your Erigon node to a CL from the start.",
